</div>}}


{{Fullscreen
|padding=2rem
|number=2
|show= <span style="color:#f2de6b">"I have one more question."</span>
|hide= <span style="color:red">Go back</span>
|content={{Blurbackground|file=Black-Screen.png}}
<div style="margin:10em; text-align:center">
"Very well," Ava adjusted her posture, moving her arms to lay by her sides rather than have them crossed.

"What was the other name you had in mind?" Clover barely could choke it out, leaving it at a whisper. 

"August... yea?" The tone hadn't wavered just yet, with the still confidence Clover came to expect when they previously worked with Ava. 

"There was one other, what was it?" Clover watched Ava struggle through an answer unable to recall the truth. Clover had their own truth to struggle through, as they forced themselves to accept a reality that was different that what they wanted. This wasn't Ava. Clover passed by Ava, watching her closely as they'd approach their bag. From it, they grabbed a blade. "What was the other name?" Clover stated again, and the other fell silent. 

With enough certainty. Clover swung at Ava, the blade barely missing her. Ava swung back, nailing Clover in the shoulder. Clover could feel the pain fade away as it was replaced with adrenaline, and a profound level of aggression. Again, they swung, striking Ava's side with the dagger. She yelped out in agony, loud enough to jolt August awake. 

"What the-!" Still lapsing in and out of consciousness, August watch Clover and the creature brawl. Blow after blow Clover tore into Ava's skin, revealing a grimy and inhuman interior. August knew it to be one of the monsters, so he pulled himself out of his bed roll and grabbed his gun.

<big>BANG</big>

In a single shot, Ava crumpled to the ground, her disguised now tattered into its proper form. In silence, they watched her die, Clover's heavy breaths filling in the gaps of the monster's groans and grunts. 



